programme.title: The Yearling
programme.desc: A sensitive teenager grows up with a pet fawn in the Florida wilderness in the 1930s.

programme.title: Love's Everlasting Courage
programme.desc: Farmer Clark Davis struggles to repay a loan and save his land during a drought. Making matters worse, his wife becomes gravely ill after agreeing to take a job in order to bring in more income.

programme.title: The Nanny Express

programme.title: My George

programme.title: Mr. Write

programme.title: What I Did for Love
programme.desc: After a lawyer (Jeremy London) proposes to his girlfriend (Dorie Barton), they head to her family's ranch for the holidays, where he must gain approval from her difficult dad (James Gammon) and cope with her scheming aunt (Sally Struthers), who informs her niece's ex-flame of the blossoming relationship. Mark Griffiths directed.

programme.title: Always and Forever

Max Gail and Rob Boltin also star. Directed by Kevin Connor.
